post_text: Thank you to all of the families who came to Back to School. If you have not come, please call the school to get an appointment this week. You will get all school supplies, books and technology to start school next week. All students and families will get trained on the technology. Every family that completes all the stations will be entered into a raffle drawing for a $50 Target gift card each day. If you have not come this week, please call the office for an appointment at 612-248-8240. We are doing appointments to ensure everyone is able to safely socially distance. Pictured here are two students learning how to set up their devices to their new internet hotspot. Other stations included training about the learning platforms, signing up for school-wide communication systems and taking a reading test. It was so great to see everyone!

post_text: This week at Back to School appointments, every student is receiving a daily schedule. Online learning for each student includes daily live lessons with two teachers in each class, individualized asynchronous learning in reading and math, independent reading time, and time for study in Spanish, Arabic, Art, and Physical Education. Depending on needs, students will have individualized online meetings with services such as Occupational Therapy, English Language Development. Reading Intervention, Speech , Mental Health, Social Work, Adaptive PE or Special Education services. Even though this is an unusual year for students across the globe, NECP students' rigorous work continues.

post_text: This week, at their Back to School appointment, Northeast College Prep students in Kindergarten through Fourth grade will receive a Clever badge. Students and families can scan the badge with their Ipad, and it will bring them to their individualized learning - live Zoom classes with teachers and learning sites, already logged in for the individual student. This will allow even the youngest learners to be more independent in accessing school and make at home learning a little simpler for families.

post_text:
How are students and families getting ready for the school year this year?
Attending a Back to School appointment this week is one way. Students will pick up their device (iPad tablet or Chromebook laptop), and school supplies like math workbooks, white boards, manipulatives and books for reading. At the appointment students will take a reading assessment, while parents complete paperwork and sign up for a virtual home visit. Parents and students will receive individualized training on their device and on the platforms they will be using in distance learning. Student who need them will receive reusable masks. Northeast College Prep staff are looking forward to seeing each student and family!
What other ways are you getting ready for the school year?

If your family is not sure when your appointment is, please call the school (612-248-8240).

NECP staff are proud and honored to have continued to work with and help support our NECP families and students. Here are some of the amazing things that have been happening during distance learning:

- More than 12,000 meals delivered and hundreds of pounds of Sheridan Story non-perishable food also passed out

- More than 250 devices prepped and handed out/delivered

- More than 3,000 Seesaw and Google Classroom lessons prepared

- Countless zoom calls, texts, phone calls, Google Meets to ensure student engagement

- More than 2,000 check in phone calls made

We are so thankful and excited to continue to support our NECP community during the summer!

Thank you to everyone for supporting our school and our students during this school closure time! Every week, we are calling families to ask what they need. Then, staff members purchase and deliver items like soap, toilet paper, and food to families. This is in addition to the breakfast and lunch meal deliveries and the addition Mojo Coffee meals that are being delivered. Here is an article in the Northeaster sharing what we are doing. We have raised almost $6,000 so far. Thank you to everyone who has donated, shopped, or volunteered in some way to help us get our families what they need!

Check out this website for the entire Northeaster. https://www.mynortheaster.com/wp-content/news-archives/200422Northeaster/#page=12

Are you looking for meaningful activities for your students to do while they're at home? Human Rights Campaign's Welcoming Schools is offering a book and a related activity every Wednesday for families to use with elementary school students at home.

Featured books and activities will focus on Welcoming Schools themes of embracing all families, being an ally and respecting differences while keeping children engaged and supported during this challenging time.

Use this link for more information and to find online versions of all the books used.

https://www.hrc.org/blog/welcoming-schools-wednesdays-activities-and-resources-for-inclusive-learnin

Given the COVID-19 school closure and stay-at-home order, many NECP families are in need of cleaning supplies and other household items. The NECP team is working to gather and distribute as many essential items as possible. If you are able, please consider donating to support these efforts. Donations can be made through the NECP website, https://northeastcollegeprep.org/. Simply click on "Donate" in the top right corner and designate "cleaning supplies" in the Notes section before submitting your donation. If you prefer not to donate online, you can mail a donation to:

Northeast College Prep c/o Erika Sass
300 Industrial Blvd.
Minneapolis, MN 55413

Please see the photo below, which highlights the items NECP is working on gathering for families. Thank you so much for your generosity during this challenging time. If you have any questions, please email or call Zach Munson, our Social Worker, at zmunson@northeastcollegeprep.org or 612-249-5207.

post_text:
Please congratulate Aemun in the comments below!

Our founding class of 8th graders will go to high school next year! We are very proud of each of them. This fall, they participated in high school visits and learned about a variety of high schools at the school fair at NECP. Among the high schools were: Avalon, Cristo Rey, Edison, Exploration, Fridley, Hiawatha Collegiate, Park Center, Patrick Henry and St. Anthony High School.

Aemun chose Cristo Rey as the high school she would like to attend. Just this week, she found out she had been accepted.

When asked about why she chose Cristo Rey Aemun, pictured here with her acceptance letter, said, "I am mostly excited about meeting new friends and teachers and going to my job. It will help me a lot to communicate with others and experience how to work in future." Congratulations to Aemun and all of our eighth graders as they prepare for high school!

It's hard not to be able to celebrate with Aemun in person. Please join us in congratulating her in the comments below.

Cristo Rey Jesuit High School - Twin Cities

post_text:
We are proud to have received the 2019 "Seal of Excellence" from Welcoming Schools. After five years of staff training, teaching lessons, working with families, and committee work at our school to make our policies and procedures more equitable, we earned this award for creating a safe and welcoming school for all students, staff and families. Welcoming Schools is a part of the Human Rights Campaign. It is the nation's premier professional development program providing training and resources to elementary school educators to embrace family diversity, create LGBTQ and gender inclusive schools, prevent bias-based bullying, and support transgender and non-binary students. There are about 20 schools nationally who have earned this award and we are the only Minnesota school to receive the award in 2019. Congratulations Northeast College Prep! Check out the Website for more information!
http://www.welcomingschools.org/training/seal-of-excellence/

The Harold Mezile YMCA has been working with NECP students on their basketball skills throughout the year, and now the players are on a team playing against other teams! The team had their first game on Thursday, January 24th and did so well. The score was tied for majority of the game, but did end with a victory for the opposing team. Despite losing the game, the team showed INCREDIBLE sportsmanship and worked extremely well as a team. They have multiple games left this season and would love your support!

SPIRIT WEEK IS BACK!

Let's show our school spirit by having some FUN! Tomorrow kicks off NECP's second annual Spirit Week.

Here is the Spirit Week schedule:

Friday, 12/14: Spirit Day (wear NECP colors or college mascot attire)

Monday, 12/17: Pajama Day (wear pajamas or comfy clothes)

Tuesday, 12/18: Character Day (dress like a character from a book or movie)

Wednesday, 12/19: Wacky Wednesday (wear things that are mismatched or silly)

Thursday, 12/20: Dress to Impress Day (wear fancy clothes - dress, bow or necktie, blazer, top hat, etc.)

Friday, 12/21: NO SCHOOL - Start of Winter Break!

post_text: You're Invited! Northeast College Prep started a music program this year with all grades Kindergarten ‚Äì 7th! Our middle school students (6th and 7th graders) choose 8 electives during the school year. This first quarter music elective offered was Choir. The morning and afternoon choir classes will combine on Wednesday, October 17th for two identical concerts. Both concerts will be in the music room at Northeast College Prep. The first concert is from 10:05 ‚Äì 10:25 and the second concert is 1:05 ‚Äì 1:25. This is a culminating concert for quarter one Choir. Quarter two begins at the end of October with Instrumental Exploration. Quarter 3 and 4 choices include: Bucket Drumming, Music Around the World and Musical Theatre. We hope to see you on Wednesday for our first ever Northeast College Prep music concert! Click here for more details: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1pmREfSgka86Q1TLuqRFfItOuNwgeTmjAvqGVw-ovMC0/edit?usp=sharing

post_text:
Yesterday was Northeast College Prep's first Talent Show. Our first to fourth grade students showed off their talents at our first Talent Show on May 5, 2018 during Town Hall. Students sang, rapped, danced, beatboxed, told jokes, did karate, and hula hooped. Congratulations to all of our talented performers!
Congratulations to all of the students who took a risk to share their talent at Town Hall.

post_text: Thank you to Mayor Jacob Frey for coming to visit Northeast College Prep yesterday to talk with the third graders about being the mayor. This year, the third graders studied the origins of democracy and how that is reflected in modern American government. The emphasis is on rights and responsibilities all citizens have, even third graders. Thank you to Mayor Frey for answering the students questions ranging from, "What has been the most surprising thing about being the mayor?" to "What is the hardest thing you have ever done?" to "What are your goals as mayor?" The Gophers and Owls were excited to know that Jacob Frey lives in Northeast Minneapolis, only the 2nd of 48 mayors to live in Northeast Minneapolis. He talked about his commitment to making Minneapolis great so all students can have access to succeed. Thank you Mayor Frey for your visit!

post_text:
Now Hiring: Reading Corps and Math Corps
Do you know someone who is 18 years or older who wants to get teaching experience? Reading Corps and Math Corps are great opportunities for anyone who wants to teach but may not have the license or training. All of the training is provided through AmeriCorps. In Reading Corps (https://minnesotareadingcorps.org/), tutors and students read one one one with students for twenty minutes each day. Math Corps (https://minnesotamathcorps.org/) tutors work with pairs of students for 45 minutes twice a week in grades 4th - 7th to build their math skills. Tutors work with the same students and build relationships with each student / pair of students. If you are interested, visit our jobs page on our website (https://northeastcollegeprep.org/become-a-teacher/) for more information.

After conferences and two snow days, Wednesday was a busy day at Northeast College Prep. Here are some highlights:

Kindergarten visited the Children's Museum, an interactive educational museum featuring hands-on exhibits designed for kids 10 & under. Thank you to the family members who chaperoned.

Girl Scouts group, Connectz, had their last group meeting with 5th and 6th grade girls. Connectz is all about working with girls of color and with economic barriers to promote empowerment, leadership, and sisterhood. Pictures are from last week when they made slime.

post_text:
Senator Dziedzic presents a District 60 Recognition to Northeast College Prep at Festival of Nations.

District 60 Recognition

RECOGNIZING NORTHEAST COLLEGE PREP FOR THEIR COMMITMENT TO QUALITY EDUCATION

WHEREAS Northeast College Prep has strove over the past three years to provide a quality education to students in Minneapolis and

WHEREAS Northeast College Prep has attained status as an authorized International Baccalaureate (I.B.) School, and

WHEREAS the Minnesota Department of Education has designated Northeast College Prep a "high quality charter school," and

WHEREAS only the top 20% of charter schools in the state receive this designation,

NOW, THEREFORE, I, the undersigned, Senator Kari Dziedzic, recognize the efforts of the administration, teachers, and students of Northeast College Prep over the past three years, and commend them for strengthening education within our community.

Kari Dziedzic
State Senator, District 60

For the first year ever, we are competing in "Brackets for Good." This is a fundraising tournament that mirrors a basketball Final Four single-elimination bracket tournament. Northeast College Prep competes against other non-profits to advance in the tournament. If you donate $1, we get 1 point in the game.
There are six rounds. The first round lasts from March 2 - March 9th. We are competing against Minnesota Food Group in this first game. You can view the bracket here https://minnesota.bfg.org/bracket . If we advance to the next round, we may be competing for up to six weeks. Donate here: https://minnesota.bfg.org/matches?utf8=%E2%9C%93&search=northeast+college+prep
